          "criteria": "HIV cholangiopathy on imaging",
          "treatment": "Antiretroviral therapy (ART) to restore immune function (CD4 goal >200). ERCP with sphincterotomy for papillary stenosis (relieves pain and improves bile drainage). Biliary stent for dominant stricture. Treat underlying opportunistic infection: CMV (ganciclovir/valganciclovir), Cryptosporidium (nitazoxanide + ART, optimize immune recovery), Microsporidia (albendazole for E. bieneusi, fumagillin for E. cuniculi). Pain management. Ursodeoxycholic acid (UDCA) 13-15mg/kg/day for cholestasis. Prognosis: poor in advanced AIDS; improved with effective ART."
